  {
    "annotations": {
      "destructiveHint": false,
      "idempotentHint": true,
      "openWorldHint": false,
      "readOnlyHint": true,
    },
    "description": "Suggest canonical tags for a note before \`remember\` when tag choice is ambiguous.

Use this when:
- You have a note title, content, or query and want compact tag suggestions
- You want canonical project terminology without exposing lots of unrelated tags
- You want to demote temporary-only tags unless they fit the note

Do not use this when:
- You need to browse notes by tag; use \`list\` with \`tags\` filter instead
- You already know the exact tags you want to use
- You want broad inventory output but are not explicitly requesting \`mode: "browse"\`

Returns: recommendedTags ranked by relevance and usage, with canonicality/lifecycle signals and one example per tag. Optional \`mode: "browse"\` for broader inventory.

Typical next step:
- Reuse suggested canonical tags when they fit, or create a new tag only when genuinely novel.",
    "inputSchema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "properties": {
        "candidateTags": {
          "items": {
            "type": "string",
          },
          "type": "array",
        },
        "content": {
          "type": "string",
        },
        "cwd": {
          "description": "Absolute path of the project working directory. Required for project-scoped routing, vault selection, and search boosting.",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "lifecycle": {
          "enum": [
            "temporary",
            "permanent",
          ],
          "type": "string",
        },
        "limit": {
          "maximum": 50,
          "minimum": 1,
          "type": "integer",
        },
        "mode": {
          "default": "suggest",
          "enum": [
            "suggest",
            "browse",
          ],
          "type": "string",
        },
        "query": {
          "type": "string",
        },
        "scope": {
          "default": "all",
          "description": "'project' = this project's memories and attached vault notes; 'global' = only unscoped memories; 'all' = everything visible (default)",
          "enum": [
            "project",
            "global",
            "all",
          ],
          "type": "string",
        },
        "storedIn": {
          "default": "any",
          "description": "Storage-label filter. Use \`main-vault\` for main/global storage. Use \`project-vault\` for any project vault. Use \`attached\` for notes from attached external repositories only.",
          "enum": [
            "project-vault",
            "main-vault",
            "any",
            "attached",
          ],
          "type": "string",
        },
        "title": {
          "type": "string",
        },
      },
      "type": "object",
    },
    "name": "discover_tags",
    "outputSchema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "properties": {
        "action": {
          "const": "tags_discovered",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "durationMs": {
          "type": "number",
        },
        "mode": {
          "enum": [
            "suggest",
            "browse",
          ],
          "type": "string",
        },
        "project": {
          "additionalProperties": false,
          "properties": {
            "id": {
              "type": "string",
            },
            "name": {
              "type": "string",
            },
          },
          "required": [
            "id",
            "name",
          ],
          "type": "object",
        },
        "recommendedTags": {
          "items": {
            "additionalProperties": false,
            "properties": {
              "example": {
                "type": "string",
              },
              "isTemporaryOnly": {
                "type": "boolean",
              },
              "lifecycleTypes": {
                "items": {
                  "enum": [
                    "temporary",
                    "permanent",
                  ],
                  "type": "string",
                },
                "type": "array",
              },
              "reason": {
                "type": "string",
              },
              "tag": {
                "type": "string",
              },
              "usageCount": {
                "type": "number",
              },
            },
            "required": [
              "tag",
              "usageCount",
              "lifecycleTypes",
              "isTemporaryOnly",
            ],
            "type": "object",
          },
          "type": "array",
        },
        "scope": {
          "enum": [
            "project",
            "global",
            "all",
          ],
          "type": "string",
        },
        "tags": {
          "items": {
            "additionalProperties": false,
            "properties": {
              "examples": {
                "items": {
                  "type": "string",
                },
                "type": "array",
              },
              "isTemporaryOnly": {
                "type": "boolean",
              },
              "lifecycleTypes": {
                "items": {
                  "enum": [
                    "temporary",
                    "permanent",
                  ],
                  "type": "string",
                },
                "type": "array",
              },
              "tag": {
                "type": "string",
              },
              "usageCount": {
                "type": "number",
              },
            },
            "required": [
              "tag",
              "usageCount",
              "examples",
              "lifecycleTypes",
              "isTemporaryOnly",
            ],
            "type": "object",
          },
          "type": "array",
        },
        "totalNotes": {
          "type": "number",
        },
        "totalTags": {
          "type": "number",
        },
        "vaultsSearched": {
          "type": "number",
        },
      },
      "required": [
        "action",
        "mode",
        "scope",
        "totalTags",
        "totalNotes",
        "vaultsSearched",
        "durationMs",
      ],
      "type": "object",
    },
    "title": "Discover Tags",
  },
  {
    "annotations": {
      "destructiveHint": false,
      "idempotentHint": true,
      "openWorldHint": false,
      "readOnlyHint": false,
    },
    "description": "Use this when:
- \`list_migrations\` shows pending migrations that should be applied

Do not use this when:
- You have not checked pending migrations yet
- You have not previewed the migration with \`dryRun: true\`

Returns: per-vault migration results, counts, warnings, errors.

[mutating: modifies note files, git commits, may push]

Typical next step:
- Re-run \`list_migrations\` to confirm nothing is pending.",
    "inputSchema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "properties": {
        "backup": {
          "default": true,
          "description": "If true, warn about backing up before real migration",
          "type": "boolean",
        },
        "cwd": {
          "description": "Optional: limit migration to a specific project vault",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "dryRun": {
          "default": true,
          "description": "If true, show what would change without actually modifying notes. Always try dry-run first.",
          "type": "boolean",
        },
        "migrationName": {
          "description": "Name of the migration to execute (get names from \`list_migrations\`)",
          "type": "string",
        },
      },
      "required": [
        "migrationName",
      ],
      "type": "object",
    },
    "name": "execute_migration",
    "outputSchema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "properties": {
        "action": {
          "const": "migration_executed",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "dryRun": {
          "type": "boolean",
        },
        "migration": {
          "type": "string",
        },
        "vaultResults": {
          "items": {
            "additionalProperties": false,
            "properties": {
              "errors": {
                "items": {
                  "additionalProperties": false,
                  "properties": {
                    "error": {
                      "type": "string",
                    },
                    "noteId": {
                      "type": "string",
                    },
                  },
                  "required": [
                    "noteId",
                    "error",
                  ],
                  "type": "object",
                },
                "type": "array",
              },
              "notesModified": {
                "type": "number",
              },
              "notesProcessed": {
                "type": "number",
              },
              "path": {
                "type": "string",
              },
              "warnings": {
                "items": {
                  "type": "string",
                },
                "type": "array",
              },
            },
            "required": [
              "path",
              "notesProcessed",
              "notesModified",
              "errors",
              "warnings",
            ],
            "type": "object",
          },
          "type": "array",
        },
        "vaultsProcessed": {
          "type": "number",
        },
      },
      "required": [
        "action",
        "migration",
        "dryRun",
        "vaultsProcessed",
        "vaultResults",
      ],
      "type": "object",
    },
    "title": "Execute Migration",
  },
  {
    "annotations": {
      "destructiveHint": true,
      "idempotentHint": true,
      "openWorldHint": false,
      "readOnlyHint": false,
    },
    "description": "Delete an existing memory by id and clean up dangling relationships.

Use this when:
- A memory should be removed entirely
- A note is obsolete and should not remain searchable

Do not use this when:
- The note should stay but move to another vault; use \`move_memory\`
- The note should be replaced or merged; use \`consolidate\`

Returns: deleted id/title, relationship cleanup details.

Writable attachments: can delete notes in writable attached vaults.

[mutating: deletes note, cleans relationships, git commits, may push]

Typical next step:
- Use \`recall\` or \`list\` to confirm the remaining memory set is clean.",
    "inputSchema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "properties": {
        "allowProtectedBranch": {
          "description": "One-time override for protected branch checks. When true, forget can commit on a protected branch without changing project policy.",
          "type": "boolean",
        },
        "cwd": {
          "description": "Absolute path of the project working directory. Required for project-scoped routing, vault selection, and search boosting.",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "id": {
          "description": "Exact memory id. Use an id returned by \`recall\`, \`list\`, \`recent_memories\`, or \`where_is\`.",
          "pattern": "^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$",
          "type": "string",
        },
      },
      "required": [
        "id",
      ],
      "type": "object",
    },
    "name": "forget",
    "outputSchema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "additionalProperties": false,
      "properties": {
        "action": {
          "const": "forgotten",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "id": {
          "type": "string",
        },
        "project": {
          "additionalProperties": false,
          "properties": {
            "id": {
              "type": "string",
            },
            "name": {
              "type": "string",
            },
          },
          "required": [
            "id",
            "name",
          ],
          "type": "object",
        },
        "relationshipsCleaned": {
          "type": "number",
