    "description": "Use this when:
- You want the local vault state aligned with remote changes
- You suspect another machine or collaborator updated the vaults

Do not use this when:
- You only need to inspect or edit a single memory

Returns: per-vault pull/push results, deletions, additions, embedding rebuild info. Embedding failures include the error reason (e.g. quota exceeded, network error).

[mutating: git sync, may rebuild embeddings]

Typical next step:
- Use \`recent_memories\`, \`list\`, or \`recall\` to inspect newly synced changes.",
