    "description": "Remove a relationship between two memories.

Use this when:
- A previously created relationship is no longer accurate
- Two notes should remain independent

Do not use this when:
- You are adding a new connection; use \`relate\`

Returns: both ids, removed relationship details.

Writable attachments: can unrelate notes in writable attached vaults.

[mutating: modifies both notes, git commits, may push]

Typical next step:
- Use \`get\` to verify both notes now stand on their own.",
