    "description": "Use after \`recall\` + \`get\` when an existing memory should be refined instead of creating a duplicate.

Use this when:
- A stored memory is stale, incomplete, or wrong
- You recalled something useful and want to refine the same note instead of creating a duplicate

Do not use this when:
- No note exists yet; use \`remember\`
- Several notes need to be merged or retired together; use \`consolidate\`

Returns: updated id, changed fields, persistence status. On lint failure, returns action=lint_error with the list of unfixable issues.

Writable attachments: can update notes in writable attached vaults.

[mutating: rewrites note, refreshes embeddings, git commits, may push]

Typical next step:
- Use \`relate\` or \`consolidate\` if the update changes how this note connects to others.

Use \`semanticPatch\` for targeted edits (more token-efficient). Use \`content\` only for complete rewrites.",
    "inputSchema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "properties": {
        "allowProtectedBranch": {
          "description": "One-time override for protected branch checks. When true, update can commit on a protected branch without changing project policy.",
          "type": "boolean",
        },
        "alwaysLoad": {
          "description": "When true, this note loads automatically at session start and receives priority in recall and relationship expansion. Use for session anchors and critical context that should always be available.",
          "type": "boolean",
        },
        "content": {
          "description": "Full note body replacement. Use only for complete rewrites or when the note is small. Mutually exclusive with semanticPatch. Content must pass markdown lint. Auto-fixable issues are fixed automatically. Common unfixable issues: fenced code blocks need a language tag (e.g. use \`\`\`text not bare \`\`\`), and broken links are rejected. If lint fails, fix the specific issues and retry — do NOT fall back to semanticPatch for this.",
          "maxLength": 100000,
          "type": "string",
        },
        "cwd": {
          "description": "Absolute path of the project working directory. Required for project-scoped routing, vault selection, and search boosting.",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "id": {
          "description": "Exact memory id. Use an id returned by \`recall\`, \`list\`, \`recent_memories\`, or \`where_is\`.",
          "pattern": "^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "lifecycle": {
          "description": "Change lifecycle. Preserve the existing value unless you're intentionally switching it.",
          "enum": [
            "temporary",
            "permanent",
          ],
          "type": "string",
        },
        "role": {
          "description": "Change role. Preserve the existing value unless you're intentionally switching it.",
          "enum": [
            "summary",
            "decision",
            "plan",
            "context",
            "reference",
            "research",
            "review",
          ],
          "type": "string",
        },
        "semanticPatch": {
          "description": "Targeted edits to note sections. Array of {selector, operation} objects. Mutually exclusive with content. If this fails, fix the issue in your patch values and retry — do NOT fall back to full content rewrite.

selector: exactly one of { heading: "exact heading text" } | { headingStartsWith: "prefix" } | { section: "exact heading text" } | { lastChild: true } | { nthChild: 0-based-index }
operation: { op: "appendChild", value: "content" } | { op: "prependChild", value: "content" } | { op: "replace", value: "new content" } | { op: "replaceSection", value: "new section" } | { op: "replaceChildren", value: "new children" } | { op: "insertAfter", value: "content" } | { op: "insertBefore", value: "content" } | { op: "remove" }

Example — add a paragraph under ## Findings, replace body under ## Recommendation, remove ## Old Section:
[
  { "selector": { "heading": "Findings" }, "operation": { "op": "insertAfter", "value": "A new paragraph." } },
  { "selector": { "section": "Recommendation" }, "operation": { "op": "replaceSection", "value": "## Recommendation\\n\\nUpdated recommendation." } },
  { "selector": { "heading": "Old Section" }, "operation": { "op": "remove" } }
]

IMPORTANT: \`appendChild\`, \`prependChild\`, and \`replaceChildren\` do NOT work with \`heading\` selectors (headings only contain inline text, not block content). To add content under a heading, use \`insertAfter\`. To replace a full section including its body, use \`section\` + \`replaceSection\`.",
          "items": {
            "properties": {
              "operation": {
                "oneOf": [
                  {
                    "properties": {
                      "op": {
                        "const": "appendChild",
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                      "value": {
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                    },
                    "required": [
                      "op",
                      "value",
                    ],
                    "type": "object",
                  },
                  {
                    "properties": {
                      "op": {
                        "const": "prependChild",
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                      "value": {
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                    },
                    "required": [
                      "op",
                      "value",
                    ],
                    "type": "object",
                  },
                  {
                    "properties": {
                      "op": {
                        "const": "replace",
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                      "value": {
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                    },
                    "required": [
                      "op",
                      "value",
                    ],
                    "type": "object",
                  },
                  {
                    "properties": {
                      "op": {
                        "const": "replaceSection",
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                      "value": {
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                    },
                    "required": [
                      "op",
                      "value",
                    ],
                    "type": "object",
                  },
                  {
                    "properties": {
                      "op": {
                        "const": "replaceChildren",
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                      "value": {
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                    },
                    "required": [
                      "op",
                      "value",
                    ],
                    "type": "object",
                  },
                  {
                    "properties": {
                      "op": {
                        "const": "insertAfter",
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                      "value": {
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                    },
                    "required": [
                      "op",
                      "value",
                    ],
                    "type": "object",
                  },
                  {
                    "properties": {
                      "op": {
                        "const": "insertBefore",
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                      "value": {
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                    },
                    "required": [
                      "op",
                      "value",
                    ],
                    "type": "object",
                  },
                  {
                    "properties": {
                      "op": {
                        "const": "remove",
                        "type": "string",
                      },
                    },
                    "required": [
                      "op",
                    ],
                    "type": "object",
                  },
                ],
              },
              "selector": {
                "properties": {
                  "heading": {
                    "type": "string",
                  },
                  "headingStartsWith": {
                    "type": "string",
                  },
                  "lastChild": {
                    "const": true,
                    "type": "boolean",
                  },
                  "nthChild": {
                    "maximum": 9007199254740991,
                    "minimum": -9007199254740991,
                    "type": "integer",
                  },
                  "section": {
                    "type": "string",
                  },
                },
                "type": "object",
              },
            },
            "required": [
              "selector",
              "operation",
            ],
            "type": "object",
          },
          "type": "array",
        },
        "summary": {
          "description": "Git commit summary only. Imperative mood, concise, and focused on why the change matters.",
          "type": "string",
        },
        "tags": {
          "description": "Optional tags for later filtering. Use a small number of stable, meaningful tags.",
          "items": {
            "type": "string",
          },
          "type": "array",
        },
        "title": {
          "description": "Specific, retrieval-friendly title. Prefer the concrete topic or decision, not a vague label.",
          "maxLength": 500,
          "type": "string",
        },
      },
      "required": [
        "id",
      ],
      "type": "object",
    },
